CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1960, pg. A2, reads: "HOFFA GREETED - More than 1,600 teamsters, a portion of the crowd shown above, turned out last Sunday at Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall to greet Teamster Union President James F. [sic] (Jimmy) Hoffa. Included in crowd were more than 100 members of Local 609, a predominantly Negro group headed by William E. (Bill) Miller. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: James R. "Jimmy" Hoffa, speaking at podium for teamsters rally in Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall
